            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                <head>No. 15.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Ayres</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 3, 1888</date>. (Received November
                        26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 182.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform the Department the
                    regular session of the recent Argentine Congress closed the 29th ultimo. In view
                    of the pressing importance of certain measures, embracing the charters of a”
                    number of projected railroads, greatly needed for the increasing traffic of this
                    growing country, President Celman has called an extra session of Congress, which
                    met the 1st instant. It is now thought this session will close sometime the
                    latter part of November.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bayless W. Hanna.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
